UPDATE

Syntax: update
        update <file>

Destructs and reloads a single file.

FORMS

  update
    With no argument: reloads the current room.  Moves all players to
    the void, destructs the room, reloads it, and moves everyone back.

  update <file>
    Destructs the object loaded from <file> and loads a fresh version.
    Path is relative to your current working directory.
    Examples:
      update /daemon/chat
      update /cmds/mortal/_who
      update /domains/Praxis/areas/splynn/splynn_entry

NOTES

  The file argument should NOT include the .c extension.
  update works for any file you have write access to.
  Available to Admin wizards only (position arch or head arch).

  For bulk updates of many files, use 'warmboot':
    warmboot <domain>   : reloads all files in a domain
    warmboot            : reloads all currently-loaded daemons

